            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/budsjett_klimaprofil.html?id=619025" title="">
                        Stronger focus on climate change in development policy
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[05.10.2010]</p>
                <p>The Government will allocate NOK 27.1 billion (USD 4.6 billion) to the fight against poverty in 2011. Increased efforts to promote clean energy and support adaptation to climate change will put a stronger focus on climate change.</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/naervaer_utlandet.html?id=620269" class="ISI_IGNORE">
                <img src="/upload/UD/Ingressbilder/Kgl_no_amb.jpg" alt="" class="ArticleImg" />
            </a>
            <div class="ArticleImgContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/naervaer_utlandet.html?id=620269" title="">
                        Changes in Norway’s diplomatic presence abroad
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[05.10.2010]</p>
                <p>The Ministry of Foreign Affairs will increase its diplomatic presence in a number of countries in 2011, for example in Brazil, India, Indonesia, China and Russia. In order to free resources for these new missions, five missions will be closed, and there will be staff reductions at some other missions next year.</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/midler_hellas.html?id=616298" title="">
                        Agreement with Greece on the allocation of the EEA and Norway Grants for 2009–2014 
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[01.10.2010]</p>
                <p>Norway and Greece have agreed on the allocation of the EEA and Norway Grants for the period 2009–2014. The asylum area is a priority sector, and will receive NOK 152 million over the five-year period. </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/forhandlinger_fred.html?id=615763" class="ISI_IGNORE">
                <img src="/upload/UD/Ingressbilder/jgs_NY_AHLC210910.jpg" alt="Foreign Minister Støre chaired a meeting of the Ad Hoc Liaison Committee for assistance to the Palestinians in New York 210910. Photo: R.Imerslund, MFA, Oslo" class="ArticleImg" />
            </a>
            <div class="ArticleImgContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/forhandlinger_fred.html?id=615763" title="">
                        Norway urges parties to continue Middle East peace talks
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[29.09.2010]</p>
                <p>The peace talks between Israel and the PLO have entered a critical phase now that Israel has decided not to extend its partial moratorium on the construction of settlements in the West Bank. “I urge Israel and the Palestinians to do their utmost to make it possible to continue the negotiations,” said Foreign Minister Jonas Gahr Støre.</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/kontaktpunkt_leder.html?id=615756" title="">
                        Hans Petter Graver to head new OECD National Contact Point 
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[29.09.2010]</p>
                <p>Professor Hans Petter Graver has been appointed head of the new Norwegian National Contact Point for the OECD Guidelines for Multinational Enterprises. Foreign Minister Jonas Gahr Støre commented, “I am delighted that four such competent people have agreed to act as the contact point that will monitor Norwegian companies’ compliance with the OECD Guidelines.” </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/pm_gavi.html?id=614806" title="">
                        Norway to donate NOK 1.4 billion to the Global Fund to Fight AIDS, Tuberculosis and Malaria 
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[22.09.2010]</p>
                <p>Norway is to increase its contribution to the Global Fund to Fight AIDS, Tuberculosis and Malaria by NOK 75 million, making the total Norwegian contribution NOK 450 million per year. This is equivalent to an increase of 20%, and it means that Norway will donate almost NOK 1.4 billion to the Fund over the next three years.   </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/palestinsk_statsdannelse.html?id=614710" title="">
                        Palestinian State Ready in Near Future
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[21.09.2010]</p>
                <p>The international donor group in support of the Palestinians (AHLC) today reconfirmed its support for the Palestinian government program that aims to establish a Palestinian state by August 2011.  </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/kyststater_afrika.html?id=614650" title="">
                        Norway signs agreement with coastal states in Africa
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[21.09.2010]</p>
                <p>Minister of the Environment and International Development Erik Solheim will sign an agreement with six countries in Africa that will help them to gain jurisdiction over their own oil and gas resources. </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/nomangedobler.html?id=614537" title="">
                        Norway redoubles its support for flood victims in Pakistan
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[19.09.2010]</p>
                <p>Norway has decided to increase its assistance for the flood victims in Pakistan to USD 66 million. The situation is critical, and the number of victims keeps rising. The floods are the worst ever in the history of Pakistan. </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/bachelet_sjef.html?id=614312" title="">
                        Norway congratulates new UN head of gender equality
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[15.09.2010]</p>
                <p>Norway congratulates Chile’s former President Michelle Bachelet on her appointment as head of the UN’s new entity for gender equality and the empowerment of women (UN Women).   </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/aleh_byabenin.html?id=613687" title="">
                        Belarus. Opposition activist Aleh Byabenin’s death
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[06.09.2010]</p>
                <p>“We extend our condolences to Aleh Byabenin’s loved ones at this difficult time. I would also like to stress that it is important that the circumstances surrounding his death are clarified quickly and thoroughly,” Foreign Minister Jonas Gahr Støre commented.   </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/vestbredden_drap.html?id=613325" title="">
                        Norway condemns killing of four Israeli citizens
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[01.09.2010]</p>
                <p>On Tuesday 31 August, four Israeli citizens were shot dead close to the Israeli settlement of Kiryat Arba on the West Bank. Hamas has taken responsibility for this outrage, which took place on the day before the start of negotiations between Israel and the Palestinians in Washington.</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/fredsforhandlinger.html?id=612752" title="">
                        Direct peace talks between Israel and the Palestinians
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[20.08.2010]</p>
                <p>«I welcome the news that the US has invited Israel and the Palestinians to resume direct talks,» said Foreign Minister Jonas Gahr Støre. «Norway urges the parties to respond positively to the US invitation, and to seize this opportunity to make progress in the negotiations. This will put the peace process back on track.»</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/gavi_styreleder.html?id=612352" title="">
                        Norwegian candidate for Chair of GAVI Alliance Board
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[13.08.2010]</p>
                <p>The Norwegian Government has nominated Dagfinn Høybråten (Member of the Storting and Leader of the Christian Democratic Party) as candidate for Chair of the Board of the GAVI Alliance.  </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/flom_millioner.html?id=612308" title="">
                        Norway to provide NOK 100 million to flood victims in Pakistan
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[12.08.2010]</p>
                <p>Norway is increasing its support for flood victims in Pakistan to NOK 100 million. The flood has affected 14 million people, six million of whom are in need of emergency food assistance. So far, 288.000 homes have been washed away.    </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/mostafaei_sikkerhet.html?id=612010" title="">
                        Foreign Minister Støre pleased that Mostafaei is safe
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[08.08.2010]</p>
                <p>“I am very pleased that human rights lawyer Mohammad Mostafaei is now safe in Norway,” said Foreign Minister Jonas Gahr Støre.    </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/flom_pakistan.html?id=611896" title="">
                        Norway gives NOK 30 million to flood-ravaged Pakistan
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[03.08.2010]</p>
                <p>Pakistan is experiencing its worst floods in 80 years. According to the UN, over a million people are affected by the flooding, and reports suggest that almost 1100 people have lost their lives. “Norway is providing NOK 30 million to support emergency relief efforts during this critical phase,” Foreign Minister Jonas Gahr Støre said.   </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/eea-ny-avtale.html?id=611778" class="ISI_IGNORE">
                <img src="/upload/UD/Ingressbilder/eea_grants.jpg" alt="" class="ArticleImg" />
            </a>
            <div class="ArticleImgContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/eea-ny-avtale.html?id=611778" title="">
                        New agreement on EEA financial mechanisms signed
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[28.07.2010]</p>
                <p>Norway and the EU have reached agreement on a financial contribution of close to NOK 15 billion for the period 2009–2014.</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/norge-hilser-kosovo-erklaring-velkommen.html?id=611664" title="">
                        Norway welcomes the Advisory Opinion of the International Court of Justice in the Kosovo Proceedings
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[22.07.2010]</p>
                <p>Norway welcomes the clear advisory opinion delivered today by the International Court of Justice in The Hague on the question of the Accordance with International Law of the Unilateral Declaration of Independence by the Provisional Institutions of Self-Government of Kosovo (request for advisory opinion).</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/utenriksmin_afghanistan.html?id=611478" title="">
                        Norwegian Foreign Minister visits Afghanistan 
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[18.07.2010]</p>
                <p>Sunday 18 July was the first day of the Norwegian Foreign Minister’s visit to Afghanistan, during which he will visit the Norwegian forces in Northern Afghanistan and participate in the important International Conference on Afghanistan in Kabul.</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/uganda.html?id=611319" class="ISI_IGNORE">
                <img src="/upload/UD/Ingressbilder/Uganda_kart.jpg" alt="" class="ArticleImg" />
            </a>
            <div class="ArticleImgContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/uganda.html?id=611319" title="">
                        Norway condemns terrorist actions in Uganda
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[12.07.2010]</p>
                <p>Norway condemns the terrorist actions in Uganda’s capital, Kampala, where at least 74 innocent people were killed and many others injured on Sunday evening. Norwegian Foreign Minister Jonas Gahr Støre commented: “We strongly condemn such terrorist actions.”</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/sahel.html?id=611289" class="ISI_IGNORE">
                <img src="/upload/UD/Ingressbilder/sahel_istock_100x75.jpg" alt="From Sahara. Photo: Istockphoto" class="ArticleImg" />
            </a>
            <div class="ArticleImgContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/sahel.html?id=611289" title="">
                        Norway’s support to drought victims in eastern Sahel increased 
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[09.07.2010]</p>
                <p>Ten million people in eastern Sahel are affected by drought and food shortages. Norwegian Minister of Foreign Affairs Jonas Gahr Støre commented: “The situation is very serious for the population in this area. We have therefore decided to increase our support to NOK 50 million.”</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/cuba-2.html?id=611241" title="">
                        Norway welcomes the release of political prisoners in Cuba 
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[08.07.2010]</p>
                <p>Norwegian Foreign Minister Jonas Gahr Støre commented: “Norway, together with the EU, has steadfastly demanded the unconditional release of political prisoners in Cuba. We were very pleased to receive the news today that the Cuban authorities will release 52 political prisoners.”</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/cbss.html?id=610696" title="">
                        Norway takes over presidency of the Council of the Baltic Sea States
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[01.07.2010]</p>
                <p>Norway has taken over the presidency of the Council of the Baltic Sea States. This means that the Norwegian Foreign Minister will serve as president of the council for one year.  </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/gaza_blokade.html?id=609174" title="">
                        Positive that Israel has decided to ease Gaza blockade 
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[21.06.2010]</p>
                <p>“It  is positive that Israel has now decided to ease the blockade of Gaza. In my view, the blockade is counterproductive because it directly affects the civilian population and undermines the forces on the Palestinian side that are interested in peace. Moreover, it does not serve to enhance Israeli security,” said Foreign Minister Jonas Gahr Støre.   </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/kirgisistan_hjelp.html?id=609173" title="">
                        Norway to give NOK 10 million in humanitarian aid to Kyrgyzstan
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[21.06.2010]</p>
                <p>“I am concerned about the situation in Kyrgyzstan. Large numbers of people in the south of the country have been caught up in the recent violence, resulting in urgent humanitarian needs. Norway stands ready to help those who are being affected by this difficult situation,” said Foreign Minister Jonas Gahr Støre.   </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/gjenoppbygging_haiti.html?id=609002" title="">
                        Norway joins Commission in charge of Haiti’s recovery and development
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[18.06.2010]</p>
                <p>Norway will be an important partner for Haiti in the country’s reconstruction efforts following the disastrous earthquake in January.   </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/iran_kritikk.html?id=608466" title="">
                        Norway endorses strong criticism of Iran in the Human Rights Council
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[15.06.2010]</p>
                <p>In the UN Human Rights Council today, Norway criticised the human rights situation in Iran on behalf of more than 50 countries. The joint statement was timed to coincide with the one-year anniversary of the controversial presidential election in Iran.</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/pm_agatha.html?id=608340" title="">
                        Norway provides NOK 7.6 million for emergency relief following tropical storm Agatha
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[14.06.2010]</p>
                <p>Norway is to provide emergency relief for Guatemala following tropical storm Agatha.</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/sandsekker.html?id=607679" title="">
                        Norway to send 323 000 sandbags to flood-stricken Hungary
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[09.06.2010]</p>
                <p>This week, Norway is to send 323 000 sandbags to flood-stricken Hungary. Heavy rains have caused extensive flooding in Central Europe in recent weeks.</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/fn_gransking.html?id=606812" title="">
                        Norway voted in favour of UN resolution on an international investigation of Israel’s boarding 
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[02.06.2010]</p>
                <p>The UN Human Rights Council has decided to establish an independent fact-finding mission to investigate the Israeli boarding of a convoy of ships carrying humanitarian assistance to Gaza. Norway voted in favour of the fact-finding mission.</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/pm_gransking.html?id=606557" title="">
                        Norway supports the Security Council’s demand for a investigation of the Israeli operation
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[01.06.2010]</p>
                <p>In a statement dated 31 May, the UN Security Council condemns the acts that led to the loss of civilian lives when Israeli naval forces boarded the convoy carrying humanitarian assistance to Gaza. The statement underscores the need for a prompt, impartial and credible investigation of the incident.  </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/pm_sudan.html?id=606518" title="">
                        First Norwegian Foreign Minister to visit Sudan for 35 years
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[01.06.2010]</p>
                <p>“The peace process in Sudan is in a decisive and critical phase. We can already see that this will be a key issue on the international agenda the next 12 months,” commented Norwegian Minister of Foreign Affairs Jonas Gahr Støre, who has started a visit to Sudan.  </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/granskning_israel.html?id=606513" title="">
                        Norway calls for an international investigation of Israel’s boarding of the convoy
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[31.05.2010]</p>
                <p>“Norway is shocked that Israeli naval forces have shot and killed civilians while boarding a convoy carrying humanitarian supplies to Gaza. I condemn this use of military force against civilians,” said Foreign Minister Jonas Gahr Støre.  </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/kampala_icc.html?id=606488" title="">
                        Kampala Review Conference a milestone in the history of international criminal law
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[31.05.2010]</p>
                <p>The States Parties to the Rome Statute of the International Criminal Court (ICC) gathered in Kampala, Uganda, to take stock of the progress of the Court. “This is a milestone in the history of international criminal law,” commented Foreign Minister Jonas Gahr Støre.   </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/nedrustning.html?id=606135" title="">
                        Norway welcomes agreement on disarmament
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[29.05.2010]</p>
                <p>In New York agreement was reached between 189 countries on the way forward for disarmament efforts. This includes concrete steps to eliminate nuclear weapons, strengthen non-proliferation efforts and create a platform that respects the right of all countries to peaceful use of nuclear technology. The Norwegian Minister of Foreign Affairs welcomes this agreement.</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/gaza_innsats.html?id=605980" title="">
                        Foreign Minister Støre says blockade of Gaza undermines the Palestinian Authority
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[27.05.2010]</p>
                <p>A flotilla of passenger and cargo ships is on its way to Gaza carrying aid supplies for the reconstruction of Gaza after the 2008–2009 war. “The ships bound for Gaza are a powerful expression of the frustration felt by the international community over the lack of progress in the reconstruction of Gaza", said Foreign Minister Jonas Gahr Støre. </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/homofilidom.html?id=605513" title="">
                        Norway concerned about prison sentence for homosexuality
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[22.05.2010]</p>
                <p>In a joint declaration with the EU, Norway expresses concern following the sentencing of a homosexual couple in Malawi to 14 years’ imprisonment.  </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/innsats_zimbabwe.html?id=605435" title="">
                        Norway to increase humanitarian assistance to Zimbabwe 
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[20.05.2010]</p>
                <p>Norway is to increase its humanitarian assistance to Zimbabwe in 2010 by NOK 10 million, to NOK 30 million. This increase is due to the situation in Zimbabwe, which is cause for grave concern. </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/pm_morales.html?id=605005" title="">
                        Bolivian President to visit Norway
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[18.05.2010]</p>
                <p>The President of Bolivia, Evo Morales, will be making an official visit to Norway from 19 to 21 May. Minister of the Environment and International Development Erik Solheim will host the visit.</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/pm_geneve.html?id=604834" title="">
                        More than 60 countries have agreed to the Oslo Commitments on Armed Violence 
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[12.05.2010]</p>
                <p>Armed violence is a global threat to stable and peaceful development. At a conference in Geneva more than 60 countries agreed to concrete measures to address armed violence.  </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/rnb_haiti.html?id=604529" title="">
                        Norway increases aid to Haiti
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[11.05.2010]</p>
                <p>The Government has proposed increased funding to Haiti in its revised budget for 2010. “We are increasing our support for reconstruction after natural disasters by NOK 50 million,” Minister of the Environment and International Development Erik Solheim commented.   </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/pm_atomsikkerhet.html?id=601790" title="">
                        White paper on nuclear safety presented today
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[23.04.2010]</p>
                <p>Today the Government will present a white paper on nuclear safety cooperation with Russia in the High North. “Our efforts to ensure that Russian nuclear waste does not harm the environment or fall into the hands of terrorists have made Norway safer. The white paper gives an overview of the concrete results that have been achieved through this cooperation,” said Foreign Minister Jonas Gahr Støre.</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/kina_jordskjelv.html?id=601046" title="">
                        Norway provides assistance to China following earthquake
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[20.04.2010]</p>
                <p>Norway is providing NOK 2 million to China following the earthquake on 14 April. The money is to go to the Chinese Red Cross.   </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/giverlandsmote_madrid.html?id=600235" title="">
                        AHLC meeting in Madrid
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[13.04.2010]</p>
                <p>The Minister of Foreign Affairs noted that the Palestinian economy is stronger than it has been in a long time. This is reducing the Palestinians’ aid dependency.  </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/haiti_bistand.html?id=599608" title="">
                        Norway pledges USD 135 million in assistance to Haiti
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[31.03.2010]</p>
                <p>Norway will provide assistance totalling NOK 800 million (USD 135 million) to Haiti over the next four years. The announcement was made by State Secretary Ingrid Fiskaa in New York today.</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/mr_forslag.html?id=599382" title="">
                        Norwegian proposal on protection of human rights defenders adopted
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[25.03.2010]</p>
                <p>Yesterday, the UN Human Rights Council unanimously adopted a Norwegian proposal on strengthening protection of human rights defenders all over the world.     </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/unicef_leiar.html?id=597686" title="">
                        Norway congratulates new head of UNICEF
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[17.03.2010]</p>
                <p>Norway congratulates Anthony Lake on his appointment as new head of the UNICEF.  UNICEF is an important partner for Norway in its efforts to promote children’s rights.  </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/israel_protest.html?id=595096" title="">
                        Foreign Minister Støre protests against Israel’s settlement expansion in East Jerusalem
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[10.03.2010]</p>
                <p>On Tuesday, Israel announced plans to build 1600 new housing units in East Jerusalem. “Norway deeply deplores Israel’s expansion of its settlement in East Jerusalem", says Foreign Minister Jonas Gahr Støre.   </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/pressesenter/pressemeldinger/2010/valget_irak.html?id=594830" title="">
                        Foreign Minister Støre comments on election in Iraq
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[08.03.2010]</p>
                <p>Foreign Minister Jonas Gahr Støre commended the people of Iraq for turning out to vote in the parliamentary election on 7 March 2010.</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
 
           
        </div>  
       
         


